articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Britain on Monday pledged to continue its support for democratic and economic reforms in Moldova after pro-Western incumbent Maia Sandu claimed victory at Sunday's closely-fought presidential election.
articles.title: UK pledges continued support for Moldova's democratic reform after presidential election

articles.author: Tom Balmforth, Alexander Tanas
articles.description: Neither Maia Sandu nor Alexander Stoianoglo, who was backed by the pro-Russian Socialist Party, has claimed victory or admitted defeat.
articles.title: Moldova's pro-Western Sandu claims election win after meddling allegations

articles.author: Susana Vera, Raul Cadenas
articles.description: The government is facing rising discontent over its response to the catastrophe that has killed at least 217 people.
articles.title: Spain deploys 7,500 troops to flood zone where anger rises at slow help

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German Foreign Minister Annalena Baerbock said on Monday that Ukraine needs support to ensure its very survival as Kyiv heads into its third winter of war exacerbated by North Korean weapons aid and massive Russian airstrikes on civilian infrastructure.
articles.title: German foreign minister vows support as Ukraine enters third winter of war

articles.author: Andreas Rinke, Miranda Murray
articles.description: Opening a crunch week that could prove fatal to Germany's tottering government, a senior party ally of Chancellor Olaf Scholz said he was optimistic of finding a budget agreement with the three-party coalition's wayward finance minister.
articles.title: German budget deal to save coalition is possible, Scholz ally says

articles.author: Hernan Nessi
articles.description: Argentina's libertarian president, Javier Milei, a political outsider who won election last year brandishing a chainsaw as a blunt symbol of his plans to cut spending, is defying long odds to right the embattled economy and keeping a lid on voter anger.
articles.title: Can Milei defuse Argentina's economic time bomb?

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least nine people died after Mount Lewotobi Laki-laki in eastern Indonesia erupted on Sunday, spewing explosive plumes of lava and forcing authorities to evacuate several nearby villages, officials said on Monday.
articles.title: Indonesia's Mount Lewotobi Laki-Laki volcano erupts, killing 9 people

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Quincy Jones, a major influence on American music in his work with artists ranging from Count Basie to Frank Sinatra and who then reshaped pop music by collaborating with Michael Jackson, died on Sunday at the age of 91, his publicist said.
articles.title: American music supremo Quincy Jones dies at 91

articles.author: Saurabh Sharma
articles.description: At least 36 people were killed and six were injured after a bus plunged into a gorge in the northern Indian state of Uttarakhand on Monday, an official told Reuters.
articles.title: At least 36 killed as bus overturns in India's Uttarakhand state

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German prosecutors have dropped a money laundering against Russian-Uzbek billionaire Alisher Usmanov, his lawyers said on Monday.
articles.title: German prosecutor drops money laundering investigation against billionaire Usmanov, his lawyers say
